Package: taylorDiD
Title: Modern Difference-in-Differences and Event-Study Helpers
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R:
    person("Taylor", "Mackay", , "tmackay@fullerton.edu", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: A consolidated set of helper functions for modern
    difference-in-differences and event-study estimation. Wraps the BJS
    imputation estimator (Borusyak, Jaravel, and Spiess) via 'didimputation',
    the de Chaisemartin and D'Haultfoeuille estimator via 'DIDmultiplegtDYN',
    and the Gardner two-stage estimator via 'did2s'. Encodes a consistent set
    of house-style conventions: unit-clustered standard errors, joint
    pre-trends F-tests, post-treatment average effects, a shared event-study
    result object, and publication-ready event-study plots and two-panel
    LaTeX tables.
